// Given a tree of n nodes (rooted at 1) where each node has a value,
// and q queries each asking how many nodes in the subtree of u
// have values in the range [L, R].
// Constraints: n, q <= 10^5, values <= 10^9
// Hint: Euler tour + offline sorting or merge sort tree.
// For this exercise, implement the Euler tour flattening step
// and answer queries assuming a sorted subarray is available.

